	<title>Learn Your Damn Homophones</title>
	
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" type="text/css" media="screen" title="main" charset="utf-8" />
	
</head>

<body>
<!-- If you're running IE6, or anything other than Safari 4 for that matter, and think that I care about you, then you're clearly an idiot.  Notice the proper use of "you're"; learn it, idiot. -->
<div id="container">
	<div id="content">
		<div id="header">
			<h1>I&rsquo;m tired of this shit.</h1>
			<p>It&rsquo;s about time that everyone learned their damn homophones.  If you slept your way through the fourth grade or just skipped all of the grammar lectures because you were too busy sucking off that dude in the locker room, then maybe this table will help clear up some of the fucking confusion.</p>
		</div> <!-- close: header -->
		<div id="main">
			<h2>Commonly fucked up homophones.</h2>

			<table cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<th>These</th>
					<th>&hellip;are not</th>
					<th>&hellip;the fucking same.</th>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Affect
						<p>Your horrendous grammar <strong>affects</strong> the quality of your input as an interlocutor.</p></td>
					<td>Effect
						<p>Your grammar&rsquo;s <strong>effects</strong> are so unspeakable that you should be prosecuted at <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hague">The Hague</a>.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Effect</em> is most commonly a noun; <em>affect</em> is most commonly a verb.</p></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Bare
						<p>By using improper grammar, you are laying <strong>bare</strong> your ignorance.</p></td>
					<td>Bear
						<p>I cannot <strong>bear</strong> this any longer: please, learn your damn homophones.</p></td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Capital
						<p><strong>Capital</strong> punishment should be applied to people who use improper grammar.</p></td>
					<td>Capitol
						<p>Improper grammar is not allowed inside the <strong>capitol</strong>.</p></td>
						<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: Capitol has an &lsquo;O,&rsquo; which is round like the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:USCapitolRotunda.JPG">rotunda</a> in the US Capitol Building.</p></td>	
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Complement
						<p>Brandy Ryan <strong>complements</strong> me because she is everything I&rsquo;m not.</p></td>
					<td>Compliment
						<p>I <strong>compliment</strong> Brandy Ryan on her transcendent beauty incessantly.</p></td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Discreet
						<p>If you can&rsquo;t discern the difference between homophones, then be <strong>discreet</strong>.</p></td>
					<td>Discrete
						<p>There is a <strong>discrete</strong> difference between someone who knows homophones and someone who does not.</p></td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Dual
						<p>The dual benefit of knowing homophones is that you will be able to communicate effectively and you won&rsquo;t look like a jackass.</p></td>
					<td>Duel
						<p>If you can&rsquo;t even get homophones right, imagine how you&rsquo;d do in a duel.  Let&rsquo;s just put it this way: John Wayne knew his homophones.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Duel</em> is usually deadly; <em>dual</em> is almost never harmful at all.</p></td>	
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Its
						<p>Bad grammar shall no longer rear <strong>its</strong> ugly head.</p></td>
					<td>It&rsquo;s
						<p><strong>It&rsquo;s</strong> a terrible thing to use improper grammar.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Its</em> can only be possessive; <em>It&rsquo;s</em> is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contraction_(grammar)">contraction</a> of &lsquo;it&rsquo; &amp; &lsquo;is&rsquo;.  <a href="http://www.homestarrunner.com/sbemail89.html">Strongbad</a> can explain this in further detail.</p></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Loose
						<p>The grammar gods shall let <strong>loose</strong> some horrible plague upon you should you choose to continue fucking up homophones.</p></td>
					<td>Lose
						<p>Using bad grammar is a social stigma, which makes you <strong>lose</strong> credibility.</p></td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Principal
						<p>The <strong>principal</strong> frowns upon fucking up homophones.</p></td>
					<td>Principle
						<p>Using proper grammar is a good <strong>principle</strong> to live by.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Principal</em> contains the word &lsquo;pal,&rsquo; which is a person just like the principal.</p></td>	
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Than
						<p>By fucking up homophones, you show that most fourth graders have better grammar <strong>than</strong> you.</p></td>
					<td>Then
						<p>If you can&rsquo;t write properly, <strong>then</strong> don&rsquo;t write at all.</p></td>
					<td>&nbsp;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Their
						<p><strong>Their</strong> egregious grammar sin of mixing up homophones will not go unpunished.</p></td>
					<td>There
						<p><strong>There</strong> is no excuse for fucking this up.</p></td>
					<td>They&rsquo;re
						<p><strong>They&rsquo;re</strong> just stupid if they can&rsquo;t get this.</p>
						<p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>They&rsquo;re</em> is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contraction_(grammar)">contraction</a> of <em>&lsquo;they&rsquo;</em> &amp; <em>&lsquo;are&rsquo;</em>.</p></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>To
						<p>I&rsquo;m going <strong>to</strong> ban you from speaking if you can&rsquo;t get homophones right.</p></td>
					<td>Too
						<p>The rest of the world hates you, <strong>too</strong>.</p></td>
					<td>Two
						<p>You should have learned these when you were <strong>two</strong>.</p></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Verses
						<p>The <strong>verses</strong> of the canonized Holy Text do not contain incorrect homophone usage; therefore, it is a cardinal sin to fuck them up.</p></td>
					<td>Versus
						<p>A match against good grammar <strong>versus</strong> bad grammar is like Batman fighting a baby and stealing his candy in the process.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Versus</em> can only be a preposition, so it can only take the form of &lsquo;Me versus You&rsquo; or &lsquo;This versus That&rsquo;; <em>verses</em> will almost always be a noun.</p></td>	
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Your
						<p><strong>Your</strong> grammar sucks.</p></td>
					<td>You&rsquo;re
						<p><strong>You&rsquo;re</strong> an idiot if you fuck up homophones.</p></td>
					<td><p class="hint"><strong>*Hint</strong>: <em>Your</em> can only be possessive; <em>you&rsquo;re</em> is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contraction_(grammar)">contraction</a> of &lsquo;you&rsquo; &amp; &lsquo;are&rsquo;.  See <a href="http://www.warehousecomic.com/comic_062.php">theWarehouse</a> for further explication.</p></td>
				</tr>
			</table>

			<h2>Please, learn your damn homophones.</h2>
		</div>
	</div> <!-- close: content -->
	<div id="footer">
		<div id="footercontent">
			<p>You think this is obscene?  Do you even <a href="http://xkcd.com/481/">read</a> any of the stupid shit you write?  <em>That&rsquo;s</em> obscene.</p>
			<p>Frustrated with a commonly fucked up homophone?  <a href="http://twitter.com/?status=%40homophone%20Please%20add%20this%20to%20the%20list%3A">Suggest it</a> to us so we can add it to our table.</p>
